@node INTRODUCTION "Introduction or what this program does..."
                            @{u}Introduction@{uu}

Some month ago we've released the first Version of CD-Server, which seems
to become a handy tool for all the Amiex-Sysops with CD-Drives...but as we
all know, Humans are known to make mistakes, and we have made some mistakes
in V1.00 of CD-Server. So after making some bug-fixing, we decided to give 
the world a new public Version, as we found out too many bugs in the last 
public Version.

Of course some new things have added to this new version, now it's possible
to use devices & Assings (!!!) at the same time. Now you could set an assign
to a directory of your HD and enter it in the CD-Server Icon. The User is
then able to switch to this Assigns/dirs without leaving the assigns you have
defined.
                       @{u}Main Features of CD-Server@{uu}

 - Allows Downloading/Viewing @{b}DIRECT@{ub} from CD-Rom without copying the files!

 - @{b}Full C-Shell usage@{ub}, i.e. @{b}TAB-Key@{ub} for @{b}Pathnames-Completition@{ub} (including
   Arguments like /*/*/ etc.), '@{b}!@{ub}' for shortcuts (like !l expands to LIST),
   @{b}20 Lines History-Linebuffer@{ub}, full @{b}CRSR-Key support@{ub} (including CTRL-X to
   delete the Line, CRSR left/right to walk through the Line,etc.)

 - Supports @{b}UNIX-Style@{ub} shell commands like '@{b}..@{ub}' for parent dir etc.

 - Is able to convert @{b}AmigaGuide@{ub}-files to @{b}ANSI@{ub}-Files and displays them
   like the wellknown mEGA-vIEW :)

 - Uses BBS-internal Download and MarkFile-Routines without having @{b}ALL@{ub}
   directory-pathes in all Conference-Icons!

 - @{b}Amiex V3.++@{ub} & @{"FAME" LINK FAME} (Final Amiga Mailbox Engine) compatible

 - Doesn't need any DOS-Commands, all commands are built in for safety !

 - Faster than light Dirscanning routine with exactly the same output like
   the wellknown DOpus has...

 - Assigns now supported

 - @{"Registered Version" LINK REGVERSION} has more enhancements...

@{u}Requirements for CD-Server@{uu}

Before starting the Installation, a few things have to be checked...first,do
you have a device (CD0: for example) or a directory which could be used ? 

Second, if you use a CD-Rom, make sure that the FileSystem used works 100%,
coz we found out that some PCMCIA-Roms have trouble reading the Filesizes
with the FileInfoBlock ! That may result in wrong results during the viewing.
and that's NO fault from us!

This tool needs Kickstart V2++ or higher (written under V3.1) and a full
installed and working Amiex V3.++ or @{"FAME" LINK FAME}.

             @{"Click here to read the Installation-Informations" LINK INSTALLATION}
@endnode

@node INSTALLATION "How to install CD-Server on your System"
@NEXT HOW2USE

@{u}General Installation@{uu}

Best way to install CD-Server is to use the supplied Installer-Script, but
if you want to install it "by hand" follow these steps:

1.Copy the Directory CD/ to doors: or wherever you have stored your Doors.

2.Copy the File 'CD-SERVER.HLP' to your S: directory (Online-Help)

3.Copy the File 'GUIDE2DOCPROF' to your C: directory, this Program is used
  for converting Guides to ANSI-Files.

4.Edit the CD-SERVER.INFO file to your needs, here's a list of ToolTypes:

 PACKDIR=<PATH>    <-> Here you could define a directory, which will be used
                       when converting AmigaGuide-Files to Ansi-files and to
                       pack files. If this Tooltype is not set, the T: dir
                       will be used as default setting.

 MAX_DEVICES=<NUM> <-> Here you set the maximum value of supported devices/
                       assigns for CD-Server. If this ToolType is not set, 
                       CD-Server set this to 1 and switch to a default 
                       device of 'CD0:' !

 DEVICE.<x>=<DEV>  <-> Define device number <x> as path <DEV>. I.e.:

                             DEVICE.1=CD0:
                             DEVICE.2=TREK:
                        
                       If CD-Server is not able to found at least device
                       number 1, it switch back to default device CD0: !

 NAME.<x>=<STRING> <-> Define for device nr. <x> an additional description.
                       If this Tooltype is not set, CD-Server writes as 
                       description 'N/A!'. Maximum length of the description
                       is 60 chars, longer strings will be cutted. I.e.:
        
                           NAME.1=Aminet 5 CD
                           NAME.2=StarTrek Collection, all about this cult.

5.At least, you have to built in CD-Server in your BBS-System. Please choose
  the System you are running : @{"AMIEX" LINK AMIEX_INSTALL} or @{"FAME" LINK FAME_INSTALL}.

6.Now you should be able to use CD-Server ...
@endnode

@node AMIEX_INSTALL "Installing CD-Server on an Amiex-System"
@PREV INSTALLATION
@NEXT INSTALLATION

@{u}Install to Amiex:@{uu}

1.Create an assign for CD-Server, called 'SERVER:'. A good place for this
  assign is T:, coz this normally points to RAM:T/, and therefor it is the
  faastest way. Don't be afraid, i don't copy any files to this Directory,
  CD-Server only needs this Directory to communicate with the BBS :) So a
  good choice is to put the following line into your 'user-startup':

                       ASSIGN >NIL: SERVER: T: DEFER

  If you install CD-Server via Installer, it will be done automatically.

2. Copy the File CD.INFO to your BBS:COMMANDS/BBSCMD/ drawer and adjust the
   path to CD-Server.

3. Edit all conference-Icons, in which the user should use CD-Server, and
   add a new DLPATH called:

                            DLPATH.(x)=SERVER:

   x stands for the next higher Number of DLPATHES in the desired icon,i.e.
   you have the following ToolTypes in your AMIGA.INFO conference-Icon :

                          DLPATH.1=BBS:AMIGA/UPLOAD/
                          DLPATH.2=BBS:PC/UPLOAD/

         then you type -> DLPATH.3=SERVER:

   You have to enter this Tooltype in every conference icon you would like
   to have CD-Server working...

4. Now restart Amiex, coz the Server holds all Icons in memory, and therefor
   Amiex won't recognize the changings. (CHANGE IT BYTEMASTER, IT'S SO LAME!)

That's all for installing to Amiex...

@endnode

@NODE FAME_INSTALL "Installing CD-Server on a FAME-System"
@PREV INSTALLATION
@NEXT INSTALLATION

@{u}Install to FAME:@{uu}

1. Start the SystemEditor, go into Menu 'DOORS',  and read in the File CD 
   contained in this Archive.

2. Edit the Path to CD-Server and save it in FAME:SETTINGS/DOORS/BBSCMD/.
   (Remember to install it as XIM, not FIM!!)

That's all for installation...under @{"FAME" LINK FAME} the SERVER: Assign is no longer
needed! 
@endnode

